  "text": "high rate of divergence following gene duplication is transient and would therefore contribute to divergence between species but not to polymorphism within species. This pattern of temporal changes in selective constraint can occur as a consequence of subfunctionalization of duplicate genes [CITATION_1] , but can also occur as a consequence of stabilizing selection on other types of redundant genetic elements such as transcription factor binding sites within enhancers [CITATION_2] .",
